com.apriori.reflect

Interface TypeVisitor<R,P>

  • Type Parameters:
    R - the type of value returned from visiting a type
    P - an optional context parameter that is supplied to the visitor when visiting a type

    public interface TypeVisitor<R,P>
    A visitor for generic types. This enables dynamic-dispatch-like algorithms without the if-else boiler-plate with instanceof checks and casts. To visit a type, use the main entry-point method: visit(Type, Object).

      • visit

        default R visit(Type type,
                P param)
        Visits the given type. This is the entry point and generally need not be overridden by implementing classes. This method will re-dispatch to one of the other visit methods based on the kind of given type.
        Parameters:
        type - the type
        param - the context parameter
        Returns:
        the result of visiting the given type

      • defaultAction

        default R defaultAction(Type type,
                        P param)
        The default action for visiting a type, called when visiting a type where the corresponding visit* method has not been overridden.

        The default implementation returns null.

        Parameters:
        type - a generic type
        param - the context parameter
        Returns:
        the result of visiting the given type

      • visitUnknownType

        default R visitUnknownType(Type type,
                           P param)
        Invoked when the visited type is not a known sub-type of the Type interface.

        Other visit* methods have a default implementation that calls defaultAction(Type, Object). But the default implementation of this method is different. Instead, it throws an UnknownTypeException.

        Parameters:
        type - the type
        param - the context parameter
        Returns:
        the result of visiting the given type
